13:05.634 --> 13:08.037
(birds chirping,
thunder crashing)

13:09.705 --> 13:12.275
What the hell is that?
My Boo Berry hand.

13:12.308 --> 13:13.877
I swore I'd never
wash it again,

13:13.910 --> 13:15.444
even though Lois
keeps telling me to.

13:15.478 --> 13:16.880
You should listen to her.

13:16.913 --> 13:18.447
Yeah, Peter,
that's disgusting.

13:18.481 --> 13:20.316
Oh, yeah?
Take that!
Aah!

13:20.349 --> 13:22.952
(giggles) That started
happening yesterday.

13:22.986 --> 13:24.888
To the bathroom!

13:24.921 --> 13:26.622
We got to get him
to wash that hand.

13:26.655 --> 13:28.024
Yeah. I'll text Lois,

13:28.057 --> 13:30.026
see if we can't all
come up with something.

13:30.059 --> 13:31.694
Just reply to that
last GIF she sent

13:31.727 --> 13:33.496
of the sloth putting on
the headphones.

13:33.529 --> 13:34.730
(chuckles)

13:34.763 --> 13:36.232
I love that one.

13:36.265 --> 13:38.167
Is it weird that
we're in a group text

13:38.201 --> 13:40.203
with our friend's wife
but not our friend?

13:40.236 --> 13:42.705
No, what's weird
is that your Bitmoji can walk.

13:42.738 --> 13:45.741
I'm allowed to have legs
in the phone world!

13:45.774 --> 13:47.776
(wind whistling)

13:52.248 --> 13:54.850
You know, once we're done here,
I'm never speaking to you again.

13:54.884 --> 13:56.752
Well, how the hell
was I supposed to know

13:56.785 --> 13:58.187
it was gonna
upset you so much?

13:58.221 --> 13:59.822
How? How?!

13:59.855 --> 14:02.358
You saw me spend
almost every single minute

14:02.391 --> 14:05.228
of every single day with Rupert
since I was born!

14:05.261 --> 14:07.096
And you don't--
up-up, hang on, hang on.

14:07.130 --> 14:08.497
Another hiker going by.

14:08.531 --> 14:10.166
One of us is going
the wrong way. Heh.

14:10.199 --> 14:12.735
Ha-ha-ha! When are they gonna
put in the elevator, right?

14:12.768 --> 14:13.836
Ha-ha-ha.

14:13.869 --> 14:15.171
I loved Rupert!

14:15.204 --> 14:17.106
He was the most important
thing in my life,

14:17.140 --> 14:19.442
and you willfully violated
the sanctity and trust

14:19.475 --> 14:21.577
of our friendship
when you destroyed him!

14:21.610 --> 14:23.579
Stewie... I just don't get it.

14:23.612 --> 14:25.581
You're so mature
in so many ways.

14:25.614 --> 14:27.683
You're... you're the smartest
person in the house.

14:27.716 --> 14:29.185
You're incredibly perceptive.

14:29.218 --> 14:32.021
You're wiser than people
40 times your age.

14:32.055 --> 14:34.457
Why is Rupert the one baby thing
you're hanging onto?

14:34.490 --> 14:36.459
Why are you so upset over a doll

14:36.492 --> 14:38.461
when I'm real
and I'm still here?

14:38.494 --> 14:41.030
Because Rupert was going
to be with me forever!

14:41.064 --> 14:43.967
He wasn't ever going to leave!

14:44.000 --> 14:45.868
So what? I'm not
leaving you, either.

14:45.901 --> 14:46.936
Oh, really?

14:46.970 --> 14:47.971
Brian, let's be honest.

14:48.004 --> 14:49.405
You're a middle-aged dog.

14:49.438 --> 14:51.107
You don't have
that many years left.

14:51.140 --> 14:53.576
And one day, all too soon,
I'm gonna be crying

14:53.609 --> 14:55.111
at your funeral
in an Armani suit,

14:55.144 --> 14:57.046
and people are gonna be like,
"Oh, nice suit,"

14:57.080 --> 14:58.914
and I'm gonna be like,
"Why are you talking

14:58.948 --> 15:02.085
about my awesome $2,000 suit--
my friend's dead!"

15:02.118 --> 15:03.419
Feels like that story
is less about me

15:03.452 --> 15:04.787
and more about your suit.

15:04.820 --> 15:06.990
Go to hell!
Besides, if you don't believe

15:07.023 --> 15:09.558
Rupert was real,
why are you so jealous of him?

15:09.592 --> 15:12.095
Why does it bother you
how upset I am?

15:12.128 --> 15:13.162
That...

15:13.196 --> 15:14.897
is a very good point.

15:14.930 --> 15:18.001
Damn right it is, you joyless,
fake-wisdom-spouting...

15:18.034 --> 15:20.836
Hey. Heh. When are they gonna
put in the elevator, right? Heh.

15:20.869 --> 15:23.106
Yeah. That other guy
said that to me.

15:23.139 --> 15:25.174
Nice shorts.

15:29.178 --> 15:31.147
For the record, I
would have preferred

15:31.180 --> 15:32.848
to dress as Frankenburry.

15:32.881 --> 15:34.850
That doesn't make any sense.
And this does?

15:34.883 --> 15:37.020
If anything, we all
three should've been

15:37.053 --> 15:38.787
Snap, Crackle and Pop.

15:38.821 --> 15:41.357
Yeah, we missed
an opportunity there.

15:41.390 --> 15:43.359
It's fine.
We did this wrong!

15:43.392 --> 15:45.361
Joe, it's fine. It's...
Cleveland, just ring the bell.

15:45.394 --> 15:46.762
(doorbell rings)

15:46.795 --> 15:48.864
(stilted): Oh, I wonder
who that could be.

15:48.897 --> 15:50.199
I'll get it.

15:52.468 --> 15:53.969
Oh, my God!

15:54.003 --> 15:54.970
Count Chocula!

15:55.004 --> 15:56.372
That's right.

15:56.405 --> 16:00.276
Silly rabbit,
Count Chocula
tastes grrreat!

16:00.309 --> 16:03.012
Oh, it's an honor
to meet you, sir.

16:03.046 --> 16:04.213
(scrubbing)

16:04.247 --> 16:06.215
Aah!

16:06.249 --> 16:08.317
Wh-What's happening?
We got you, Peter.

16:08.351 --> 16:10.153
Yeah, there's a golf ball
scrubber in there.

16:10.186 --> 16:11.554
Just relax and
let it happen.

16:11.587 --> 16:13.056
No! No!

16:13.089 --> 16:15.724
My miraculous
tiny life-forms!

16:17.193 --> 16:20.129
(rumbling)

16:20.163 --> 16:21.564
(creatures chittering)

16:25.868 --> 16:27.503
(screaming)

16:33.376 --> 16:34.977
Where are we
going, Father?

16:35.010 --> 16:38.047
To a place
better than this, son.

16:38.947 --> 16:40.583
FATHER and SON:
Yay!

16:40.616 --> 16:42.518
♪

16:53.796 --> 16:55.898
Well, Rupert, we made it.

16:55.931 --> 16:58.234
It's beautiful up here.

16:58.267 --> 17:00.236
So should...
should we just...

17:00.269 --> 17:02.338
sprinkle him around
randomly, or...?

17:02.371 --> 17:04.907
Oh, don't be a savage, Brian.
What is your problem?

17:04.940 --> 17:06.775
We have to have
the ceremony first.

17:08.144 --> 17:10.113
Dearest Rupert,

17:10.146 --> 17:11.547
we're here.

17:11.580 --> 17:13.582
I never wanted this to happen,

17:13.616 --> 17:16.185
and it happened
far, far too soon.

17:16.219 --> 17:17.253
But...

17:17.286 --> 17:19.388
(crying):
I can't.

17:19.422 --> 17:21.257
You... you do it.

17:21.290 --> 17:22.525
Wha... What?

17:22.558 --> 17:24.227
You give the eulogy.
I-I'm too upset.

17:24.260 --> 17:25.394
I can't.

17:25.428 --> 17:26.929
What am I supposed to say?

17:26.962 --> 17:29.365
I don't know,
Just... just tell the truth.

17:29.398 --> 17:32.935
Let-let Rupert know
how important he is.

17:32.968 --> 17:34.770
Okay, um...

17:35.771 --> 17:37.273
Rupert was...

17:37.306 --> 17:39.275
a-a great bear,

17:39.308 --> 17:41.710
uh, a great, uh...

17:41.744 --> 17:44.079
Power bottom.
Right, right, okay.

17:44.113 --> 17:47.950
But most importantly of all,
he was a great friend.

17:47.983 --> 17:50.653
He was always there whenever
Stewie needed him.

17:50.686 --> 17:52.821
He was understanding.

17:52.855 --> 17:54.823
He always listened.

17:54.857 --> 17:57.493
He made Stewie
a better person.

17:57.526 --> 17:59.395
Stewie...

17:59.428 --> 18:01.730
and I are both...

18:01.764 --> 18:04.733
incredibly grateful for all
the time we had with you,

18:04.767 --> 18:07.336
and we wouldn't change
a single moment.

18:07.370 --> 18:09.071
Except the end.

18:09.104 --> 18:10.273
Sorry about that.

18:10.306 --> 18:13.442
Um, rest in peace, Rupert.

18:13.476 --> 18:15.311
♪

18:15.344 --> 18:17.980
(wind whistling softly)

18:22.851 --> 18:25.354
Thank you, Brian.

18:25.388 --> 18:27.190
That was...

18:27.223 --> 18:29.091
that was beautiful.

18:29.124 --> 18:30.593
(takes deep breath)

